---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---
<BaseLayout
  title="About MOmery"
  description="The story behind MOmery — how a quiet piece of land in northern Minnesota became a gathering place for family, friends, and a lifetime of memories."
>
  <section class="pt-10 pb-20 px-6 max-w-3xl mx-auto bg-cream-2">
    <p class="eyebrow block mb-3">The Why</p>
    <h1 class="font-serif text-4xl md:text-5xl mb-10">About MOmery</h1>

    <div class="space-y-6 opacity-85 leading-relaxed">
      <p class="font-serif italic text-xl text-gold border-l-4 border-gold pl-5">
        Every great tradition begins with a simple idea.
      </p>

      <p>
        For Dave and Mary, it started with a quiet piece of land tucked away in the remote
        forests of northern Minnesota. Their dream wasn't to build a destination or create a
        retreat. They simply envisioned a place where they could boondock, unplug from everyday
        life, and enjoy the peace and solitude that only the Northwoods can provide.
      </p>

      <p>Year after year, they returned.</p>

      <p>
        With chainsaws, tractors, and plenty of determination, they bush-hogged trails, cleared
        brush, and slowly transformed the wilderness. They weren't entirely sure what the
        property would become&mdash;they simply knew it was worth the effort.
      </p>

      <p>Then something unexpected happened.</p>

      <p>Friends and family began showing up.</p>

      <p>
        What started as a secluded campsite gradually became a gathering place where stories were
        shared around campfires, friendships grew stronger, and memories were made that would
        last a lifetime.
      </p>

      <p>The camp itself evolved alongside those memories.</p>

      <p>
        A simple makeshift privy became a real bathroom. An outdoor shower&mdash;fed by a
        1,000-gallon water tank hauled in the back of a pickup truck&mdash;eventually gave way to
        modern comforts. Deer stands appeared throughout the woods, trails expanded, and the
        original MAS*H-style camp, warmed by nothing more than a wood stove, slowly became the
        foundation for the cabin that now welcomes so many.
      </p>

      <p>
        Not every hunting season filled the freezer. Some years the woods seemed to outsmart even
        the most experienced hunters. There were cold mornings, empty tags, plenty of laughter,
        and countless stories told beside the fire while wildlife quietly reminded everyone who
        truly belonged in these woods.
      </p>

      <p>But the hunt was never the real reason people returned.</p>

      <p>People came for each other.</p>

      <p>
        Over the years, family and friends have traveled from Minnesota, South Dakota, Kentucky,
        Texas, and beyond to spend time together&mdash;sharing meals, enjoying a favorite cigar,
        telling stories late into the night, exploring the woods, and celebrating the simple joy
        of being together far from the distractions of everyday life.
      </p>

      <p>This website exists to preserve those moments.</p>

      <p>
        MOmery is more than a collection of photographs and videos. It is a living archive of the
        people, traditions, adventures, laughter, and friendships that have made this little
        corner of Minnesota so special.
      </p>

      <p>
        Whether you have been coming here for decades or are discovering it for the very first
        time, welcome.
      </p>

      <p class="font-serif italic text-xl text-gold border-l-4 border-gold pl-5 mt-8">
        Come relive the stories. Remember the adventures. And help us preserve the memories for
        generations yet to gather around the next campfire.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
